#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:1
msgid "Atlas 300I DUO"
msgstr "Atlas 300I DUO"

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:4
msgid "Atlas 300I DUO does not support `triton` or `triton-ascend`."
msgstr "Atlas 300I DUO 不支持 `triton` 或 `triton-ascend`。"

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:7
msgid "Run vLLM on Atlas 300I DUO"
msgstr "在 Atlas 300I DUO 上运行 vLLM"

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:9
msgid "Install Notes"
msgstr "安装说明"

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:11
msgid ""
"If installing from source, `vllm` and `vllm-ascend` may automatically "
"pull in `triton` and `triton-ascend` dependencies, which may cause "
"unexpected issues on Atlas 300I DUO. Please uninstall them before running"
" on Atlas 300I DUO:"
msgstr ""
"如果从源码安装，`vllm` 和 `vllm-ascend` 可能会自动引入 `triton` 和 `triton-ascend` "
"依赖，这可能在 Atlas 300I DUO 上导致意外问题。请在 Atlas 300I DUO 上运行前卸载它们："

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:17
msgid "Graph Mode Notes"
msgstr "图模式说明"

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:20
msgid ""
"The current release supports `FULL_DECODE_ONLY` graph mode on Atlas 300I "
"DUO devices, but the following limitations apply due to hardware event-id"
" resource constraints:"
msgstr ""
"当前版本在 Atlas 300I DUO 设备上支持 `FULL_DECODE_ONLY` 图模式，但由于硬件事件ID资源限制，存在以下限制："

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:22
msgid ""
"When multiple Tensor Parallel (TP) ranks are enabled, the number of "
"capturable graphs is limited and depends on the model depth. For example,"
" Qwen3-32B can capture and replay 2 graphs."
msgstr ""
"当启用多个张量并行（TP）rank时，可捕获的图数量有限，且取决于模型深度。例如，Qwen3-32B 可以捕获并重放 2 个图。"

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:23
msgid "There is no such limitation when TP=1."
msgstr "当 TP=1 时，没有此限制。"

#: ../../source/tutorials/hardwares/310p.md:24
msgid ""
"We have reached out to the relevant experts for a solution. A software-"
"based fix is considered feasible, but full support will take additional "
"time. Thank you for your understanding."
msgstr ""
"我们已联系相关专家寻求解决方案。基于软件的修复被认为是可行的，但完全支持需要额外时间。感谢您的理解。"

